# Update App Icon

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> I found [flutter_01.png](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/flutter_01.png) in the root directory and will use it as the new app icon. If this is not the correct image, please let me know.

## Proposed Changes
### Assets
#### [NEW] [assets/images/flutter_01.png](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/assets/images/flutter_01.png)
- Move [/flutter_01.png](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/flutter_01.png) to `assets/images/flutter_01.png`.

### Configuration
#### [MODIFY] [pubspec.yaml](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/Aniruddh/Extracurricular/flutter-app/the_30sec_journal/pubspec.yaml)
- Update `flutter_launcher_icons.image_path` to `assets/images/flutter_01.png`.

### Icon Generation
- Run `dart run flutter_launcher_icons` to generate the new icons for iOS and Android.

## Verification Plan
### Automated Tests
- None.

### Manual Verification
- Run the app on the simulator/device and verify the icon has changed.
- Inspect `ios/Runner/Assets.xcassets/AppIcon.appiconset` to see updated images.
